" ============================================================
" Entries from .zedvimrc that could NOT be mapped to keymap.json
" ============================================================

" ============================================================
" VIM SETTINGS — Use Zed's settings.json instead
" ============================================================

" set clipboard+=unnamed
"   → "vim": { "use_system_clipboard": "always" }

" set scrolloff=10
"   → "vertical_scroll_margin": 10  (approximate — Zed uses pixels not lines)

" set number + set relativenumber
"   → "line_numbers": "relative"
"   → In vim settings: "toggle_relative_line_numbers": true  (absolute in insert, relative in normal)

" set ignorecase + set smartcase
"   → "vim": { "use_smartcase_find": true }

" set hlsearch + set incsearch
"   → Built-in behavior in Zed's vim mode, no setting needed.


" ============================================================
" SCROLL + CENTER — Cannot chain vim commands in keymap.json
" ============================================================

noremap <C-d> <C-d>zz
noremap <C-u> <C-u>zz
noremap n nzz
noremap N Nzz
" Zed's keymap.json does not support chaining multiple vim operations.
" No known viewport scroll-only action (ctrl-e/ctrl-y equivalent) was found
" for ctrl-j/ctrl-k remapping either — those bindings were omitted.
" ctrl-e / ctrl-y work natively in Zed's vim mode if you use them directly.


" ============================================================
" COMPLEX VIM SEQUENCES — No equivalent Zed action
" ============================================================

nnoremap J Jh
" Join lines while keeping cursor on the last character of the first line.
" No Zed action equivalent.

" Blackhole register operations — Zed's keymap actions don't expose register selection:
nnoremap x "_x
nnoremap s "_s
nnoremap c "_c
nnoremap C "_C
xnoremap c "_c

xnoremap p "_dP
" Paste in visual mode without overwriting the yank register.
" This is a complex two-step vim sequence with register selection.

xnoremap < <gv
xnoremap > >gv
" Indent and re-enter visual mode to keep selection.
" NOTE: Test this in Zed first — Zed may already re-select after indent/dedent in visual mode.

noremap gm %
" Mapped as editor::MoveToEnclosingBracket in keymap.json (normal + visual cursor jump).
" LIMITATION: Won't work as a motion for operators (e.g., d gm, y gm) because
" Zed's keymap.json has no operator-pending context.

noremap [[ [{
noremap ]] ]}
" Jump to previous/next enclosing brace. No direct Zed action equivalent.

noremap Q @q
" Run macro 'q'. No Zed action to replay a named macro.

" Operator-pending mode for gl / gh:
onoremap gl $
onoremap gh ^
" Zed keymap.json has no operator-pending context. The gl/gh bindings in
" keymap.json only work as cursor movements in normal/visual mode, not as
" motions for d, c, y, etc.

noremap + <C-a>
noremap - <C-x>
" Increment/decrement number under cursor. No confirmed Zed action name found.

" g h is mapped to editor::MoveToBeginningOfLine (equivalent to vim's `0`).
" vim's `^` (first non-whitespace) has no confirmed distinct Zed action name.
noremap gh ^


" ============================================================
" CAMEL CASE TEXT OBJECTS — No Zed equivalent
" ============================================================

nmap vic l[bv]w
nmap cic l[bv]wc
nmap dic l[bv]wd
nmap yic l[bv]wy
" These simulate camel case text objects via complex vim sequences.
" Consider a Zed extension for camel case word operations.


" ============================================================
" CONFLICTING BINDINGS
" ============================================================

map gc <Action>(GotoClass)
" CONFLICT: `gc` is the vim-commentary operator prefix in Zed's vim mode.
" Mapping gc to an action breaks gc + motion (gcc, gcj, etc.) for toggling comments.
" Alternative: use command_palette::Toggle and search for the symbol type,
" or remap to a different key like <Leader>gc.


" ============================================================
" SHELL COMMANDS — No Zed keymap equivalent
" ============================================================

map <Leader>lg :!wt lg<CR>
map <Leader>cl :!wt claude<CR>
" These open Windows Terminal with lazygit/claude.
" Workaround: Define Zed tasks in tasks.json, then bind via task::Spawn.
" Example tasks.json entry:
"   { "label": "lazygit", "command": "wt", "args": ["lg"] }
" Then bind: "space l g": ["task::Spawn", { "task_name": "lazygit" }]


